  "prompt": "What do I should expect from a 20k 3d score in AnTuTu?",
  "response": "A score of 20,000 in the 3D component of AnTuTu's benchmarking test indicates entry-level to older hardware performance for 3D graphics and gaming. This suggests that the device may not handle graphically intensive tasks very smoothly and might struggle with newer or high-end games. It will likely perform adequately with basic 3D applications, multimedia, and casual games. However, you may need to lower graphics settings to achieve smoother performance in more demanding games. Additionally, such a score usually points to a device that could be several years old or one that was designed as a budget option.",
